The paper deals with the problem of representation bias in machine learning datasets, which is a common issue in the fields of machine learning, computer vision, and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also proposes a new dataset REPAIR algorithm, which involves optimization and stochastic gradient descent, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) possible sub-categories as well.
